      "name": "Primary hemolysis index validation against FDA pump experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against published experimental measurements for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump across all five flow-speed operating points. Mean relative error of 8.3% was achieved across the operating envelope, with all predictions falling within the expanded uncertainty band of the experimental reference. The k-omega SST turbulence closure was confirmed adequate for the shear-dominated near-impeller region.",
