      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Tolerance sensitivity validation for worst-case hemolysis identification",
      "description": "A secondary validation exercise was conducted to confirm that the CFD model correctly ranks hemolysis severity across dimensional tolerance variants. Twelve geometric perturbations spanning ±0.15 mm on impeller tip clearance and volute cutwater gap were simulated. The model successfully identified the same worst-case configuration (minimum tip clearance, maximum cutwater proximity) as identified in the engineering assessment. Relative hemolysis index (RH) predictions remained below the RH < 1 acceptance threshold for all nominal configurations. The exercise provides high confidence that the model is suitable for tolerance-driven design decisions under CPB operating conditions.",
      "quantitativeOutcome": "RH < 1 for all 12 nominal variants; worst-case rank order preserved relative to engineering assessment",
      "passFail": "Pass"
    }
