    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The CFD model for CPB hemolysis prediction has been assessed against all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors at MRL 2. Seven factors were formally assessed, with all achieving required levels; six factors were appropriately scoped as not-assessed at MRL 2. The primary validation result demonstrates 8.3% mean relative error against FDA experimental data with full uncertainty characterization. The tolerance sensitivity validation confirms the model's ability to correctly identify worst-case hemolysis configurations, supporting the design decision. Assurance level is declared High based on the breadth of verification activities, order-of-accuracy confirmation, and turbulence model sensitivity analysis. The credibility package is accepted as sufficient evidence to support the regulatory submission for the Class II CPB device tolerance assessment.",
